Peru President Humala’s Approval Rating Rises to 70% in Poll

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-09-09T22:27:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/peru-president-humala-s-approval-rating-rises-to-70-in-poll.html
Peruvian President  Ollanta Humala ’s
approval rating rose to 70 percent this month from 62 percent in
August, Datum Internacional said.  Datum said 80 percent of those surveyed said they agreed
with the government’s Aug. 25 agreement with mining companies on
increasing royalties, the researcher said in an e-mailed report.
The tax accord won’t stem conflicts between mining companies and
local communities, according to 35 percent of those surveyed.  The Lima-based researcher contacted 1,222 people from Sept.
4-7 in rural and urban areas. The poll has a margin of error of
2.9 percentage points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in  Lima  at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
